30|$|Apart {{from these}} direct attacks on LoanAmt, there {{could also be}} {{indirect}} attacks launched via the sibling Collateral attribute. Specifically, the linkage between a pair of BS ciphertexts corresponding to a <b>Collateral</b> plaintext <b>value</b> (dotted line 5), or a pair of RS ciphertexts corresponding to a <b>Collateral</b> plaintext <b>value</b> (dotted line 6), {{could be used to}} launch a BSA on LoanAmt. This is prevented because physical randomization ensures the absence of row linkages between the encrypted <b>Collateral</b> columns, while <b>value</b> linkages are eliminated by the three-layered SBC-PPE-OPE encryption, using different keys for each table, as described in Sect.  3.|$|R
